					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not going to say &quot;absolutely not&quot; to four-letter opcodes, but I'd really like to avoid it if possible.<br /><br />Definitely many opcodes where it'd help a lot, had to make dbnz &lt;label&gt; into bne --y=label. There's no three-letter abbreviation for &quot;decrement and branch if not zero&quot; which makes sense, so we have to express the decrement behavior in the operand section.<br /><br />But I'm a really, really big fan of the visual symmetry that equally sized opcodes adds. It's one of my favorite features of 6502 syntax.</div>

